    <note type="biography">
        <p>Whig politician and landowner. Came into estates in 1776. Elected MP for Norfolk in same year. Retired as father of the House of Commons in 1833. Created earl of Leicester of Holkham and Viscount Coke, 1837. Bred Southdown variety of sheep and Devon cattle. Improved Suffolk breed of pigs by crossing with Neapolitan.</p></note>
